WEBVTT

00:00:01.478 --> 00:00:02.245
Alias

00:00:03.085 --> 00:00:07.118
An alias is a string we can define
that replaces a command name.

00:00:07.418 --> 00:00:11.785
Aliases are useful for replacing
commonly-used commands and switches

00:00:11.785 --> 00:00:15.585
with a shorter command,
or alias, that we define.

00:00:15.785 --> 00:00:20.051
In other words, an alias is a command
that we define ourselves,

00:00:20.051 --> 00:00:22.285
built from other commands.

00:00:23.378 --> 00:00:27.511
For example, we typically tend
to use ls -la

00:00:27.511 --> 00:00:32.145
to display results in a long list,
including hidden files.

00:00:32.145 --> 00:00:36.045
