use an alias to replace this command:

00:00:36.925 --> 00:00:39.558
By defining our own command, lsa, 

00:00:39.558 --> 00:00:45.525
we can quickly execute ls -la without
having to type any arguments at all.

00:00:46.658 --> 00:00:51.525
We can see the list of defined aliases
by running alias without arguments.
